To set up on localhost(lampp):

first start the server , command : sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start (it may vary accordingly, please follow as per your device)

Download or clone the repository : git clone https://github.com/dineshkota3/Project_cars.git

inside the Project_cars/ you will find the tindercars/

Inside the folder tindercars/ you will find the sql file i.e. localhost.sql

start the localhost server. Go to http://localhost/phpmyadmin/

There you can find the import tab which is in between export and settings. Click on that.

You will be redirected to a page where you have to upload the localhost.sql file which is present in Project_cars/tindercars

click on the browse button and upload the localhost.sql

Then scroll down to bottom, there you find Go button. Click on it.

Now sql database cars has been created with table carsid with five rows in it. Please check once.

now copy paste the tindercars folder to htdocs present in lampp folder. 

command for copy : sudo cp -r path_to_cloned_repository/Project_cars/tindercars/ /opt/lampp/htdocs

or in the terminal navigate to Project_cars folder, then execute  sudo cp -r tindercars/ /opt/lampp/htdocs

Now go to browser and type in localhost/tindercars

For Mobile:

After all the things done above , assuming that the laptop is connected to wifi.

open terminal , type in command : ifconfig

under "wlan0" you see an ipaddress of format 10.0.x.x or 192.168.x.x 

go to chrome in mobile, in url address type in 10.0.x.x/tindercars or 192.168.x.x/tindercars accordingly


